upright.tags: Diligence, responsibility, efficiency, steadfast, methodical, hardworking, reliable, pragmatic

upright.tags: Practicality, nurturing, security, stability, warmth, resourcefulness, care, abundance
upright.description:
She who bears the Coin best. Money is nothing if not to support community,
to share with those you love. The Queen of Pentacles is the queen of serving others. she knows fullness in coins by converting them to actual worth, good food with friends, mutual aid and support, and love.

reversed.tags: Overbearing, materialistic, neglectful, domineering, selfish, inconsiderate, rigid, unbalanced
reversed.description: The Queen of Pentacles might indicate a focus on material matters to the detriment of emotional or personal care.

upright.tags: Abundance, leadership, stability, prosperity, authority, success, solidity, reliability
upright.description: The King of Pentacles represents success, financial security, and a commanding presence in the material realm.

reversed.tags: Tyranny, stubbornness, poor financial decisions, mismanagement, rigidity, avarice, risk, imprudence
reversed.description: The King of Pentacles warns of mismanagement of resources or an overemphasis on material control.
